  "content": "s. On native Linux, <strong>Docker talks directly<br>\n    to the kernel</strong> &mdash; no VM tax, no memory leaks.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">04 / 08</div>\n</div>\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SLIDE 5: GPU DISCOVERY                          -->\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">GPU Surprise</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">\n    Your iGPU Is<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-amber\">Sitting Idle.</span><br>\n    Use It.\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px;\">\n    Most laptops have two GPUs. Most people only use one.<br>\n    Linux lets you assign processes to each GPU individually.\n  </div>",
